snDownloadParamsTftpServerHostName.name: snDownloadParamsTftpServerHostName
snDownloadParamsTftpServerHostName.description: IP address of the TFTP server (x.y.z.w).

snDownloadParamsFile.name: snDownloadParamsFile
snDownloadParamsFile.description: Full path name of file to be loaded from the TFTP server host. Note that the file name must have the appropriate syntax for the TFTP server host. E.g., if the TFTP server host is a UNIX machine, the full file name might be /tftp/name.lad, or if the TFTP server host is a Windows machine, the full file name might be C:\tftp\name.lad.

snDownloadParamsControl.name: snDownloadParamsControl
snDownloadParamsControl.description: Setting this object to start-load(2) causes the system to start a downloading process. Setting this object to cancel-load(3) causes the system to abort a downloading process. If ParamsProtocol is <tftp-server> the object is not writable. Reading the object, meaning-less(127) is returned.

snDownloadParamsStatus.name: snDownloadParamsStatus
snDownloadParamsStatus.description: The status of the TFTP client.

snDownloadNextBlockId.name: snDownloadNextBlockId
snDownloadNextBlockId.description: The number of the next block ID expected by the TFTP session. Block ID's are numbers starting with 1.

snDownloadParamsError.name: snDownloadParamsError
snDownloadParamsError.description: The error status of the TFTP client.

snDownloadAutoLoad.name: snDownloadAutoLoad
snDownloadAutoLoad.description: The value enabled(1) will automatically start TFTP when the Operative Program is invalid. The value disabled(2) will inhibit TFTP.

snDownloadEventLogTableFile.name: snDownloadEventLogTableFile
snDownloadEventLogTableFile.description: Full path name of file to be saved to the TFTP server host. Note that the file name must have the appropriate syntax for the TFTP server host. E.g., if the TFTP server host is a UNIX machine, the full file name might be /tftp/name.txt, or if the TFTP server host is a Windows machine, the full file name might be C:\tftp\name.txt.

snDownloadEventLogTableControl.name: snDownloadEventLogTableControl
snDownloadEventLogTableControl.description: Setting this object to start-save(3) causes the system to start a uploading process. Setting this object to cancel-(4) causes the system to abort a uploading process. If ParamsProtocol is <tftp-server> the object is not writable. Reading the object, meaning-less(127) is returned.

snDownloadConfigFile.name: snDownloadConfigFile
snDownloadConfigFile.description: Full path name of file to be saved or loaded from the TFTP server host. Note that the file name must have the appropriate syntax for the TFTP server host. E.g., if the TFTP server host is a UNIX machine, the full file name might be /tftp/name.txt, or if the TFTP server host is a Windows machine, the full file name might be C:\tftp\name.txt.

snDownloadConfigControl.name: snDownloadConfigControl
snDownloadConfigControl.description: Setting this object to start-load(2) causes the system to start a downloading process. Setting this object to start-save(3) causes the system to start a uploading process. Setting this object to cancel-(4) causes the system to abort the process. If ParamsProtocol is <tftp-server> the object is not writable. Reading the object, meaning-less(127) is returned.

snNvLogMaxEntries.name: snNvLogMaxEntries
snNvLogMaxEntries.description: Maximum number of events that can be kept in Non-Volatile Memory.

snNvLogCurrentEntries.name: snNvLogCurrentEntries
snNvLogCurrentEntries.description: Number of events that are currently kept in Non-Volatile Memory.

snNvLogNewEntries.name: snNvLogNewEntries
snNvLogNewEntries.description: Counter for events that are logged in Non-Volatile Memory. This counter starts at 0 after each system start. User can reset this counter at any time by writing 0 to this object.

snNvLogClear.name: snNvLogClear
snNvLogClear.description: Setting this object to clear(1) value, clears the events that are kept in Non-Volatile Memory.

snNvLogTable.name: snNvLogTable
snNvLogTable.description: The table contains the last events that occurred in the system.

snNvLogEntry.name: snNvLogEntry
snNvLogEntry.description: The description of an event that occurred in the system, and was stored in Non-Volatile memory.

snNvLogPowerUpCount.name: snNvLogPowerUpCount
snNvLogPowerUpCount.description: The number of times the system was powered up.

snNvLogTime.name: snNvLogTime
snNvLogTime.description: The sysUpTime of the system when the event occurred.

snNvLogSequenceNumber.name: snNvLogSequenceNumber
snNvLogSequenceNumber.description: The sequence number of the log entry.

snNvLogPositionDescr.name: snNvLogPositionDescr
snNvLogPositionDescr.description: Read - find the oid of the entry with spezial number in log table. Write - set the entry number in log table for the read request.

snSwitchTrapsEnable.name: snSwitchTrapsEnable
snSwitchTrapsEnable.description: Determines whether this device will transmit traps to SNMP management stations. This if this object is set to disable, no traps will be sent. Setting this object to enabled is a necessary, but not a sufficient condition for transmission of traps.

snTrapTimeLastGenerated.name: snTrapTimeLastGenerated
snTrapTimeLastGenerated.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the last trap was generated.

snTrapMaxManagers.name: snTrapMaxManagers
snTrapMaxManagers.description: The maximum number of managers that can be registered for receiving traps.

snTrapTable.name: snTrapTable
snTrapTable.description: This table contains information about the managers to which traps should be directed. Setting the snTrapState to inactive(3) removes the corresponding entry from the table.

snTrapEntry.name: snTrapEntry
snTrapEntry.description: This object contains runtime information about an individual trap destination.

snTrapAddress.name: snTrapAddress
snTrapAddress.description: The IP address of the network management entity to which traps should be sent.

snTrapState.name: snTrapState
snTrapState.description: The state of this entry in the trap address table. Setting this object to inactive(3) removes the corresponding entry from the table.

snUserDescription.name: snUserDescription
snUserDescription.description: Extended description of the station including user specific information. This value is used for the email From-field.

snHwVersion.name: snHwVersion
snHwVersion.description: The hardware version of the system.

snBootStrapVersion.name: snBootStrapVersion
snBootStrapVersion.description: The firmware version of the boot software installed in the system.

snSwVersion.name: snSwVersion
snSwVersion.description: The firmware version of the system.

snInfoOrderNr.name: snInfoOrderNr
snInfoOrderNr.description: The order number of this product.

snSerialPortSpeed.name: snSerialPortSpeed
snSerialPortSpeed.description: The serial port speed in bits per second.

snSwitchTelnetTimeOutEnable.name: snSwitchTelnetTimeOutEnable
snSwitchTelnetTimeOutEnable.description: Enables or disables the time out for a TELNET session.

snSwitchTelnetTimeOut.name: snSwitchTelnetTimeOut
snSwitchTelnetTimeOut.description: Time out for the TELNET session. The time could be set in steps of 10 seconds. Minimum value is 60 seconds, maximum value is 600 seconds.

snSwitchSNMPEnable.name: snSwitchSNMPEnable
snSwitchSNMPEnable.description: Determines whether this device may be accessed by SNMP management stations.

snSysReset.name: snSysReset
snSysReset.description: Resets the system. cold-reset(1) is identical to Power-On-Reset or Watchdog-Reset. warm-reset(2) is identical to restart command.

snResetPowerUpCount.name: snResetPowerUpCount
snResetPowerUpCount.description: The number of times the sytem was powered up.

snEraseDataStoreFlash.name: snEraseDataStoreFlash
snEraseDataStoreFlash.description: Erase all configuration data and log table entries. In opposite to reset to factory defaults nothing is saved.

snEmailSMTPIpAddress.name: snEmailSMTPIpAddress
snEmailSMTPIpAddress.description: IP address or host name of SMTP server.

snEmailSMTPPort.name: snEmailSMTPPort
snEmailSMTPPort.description: Number of TCP port to which the SMTP server will listen.

snEmailEnable.name: snEmailEnable
snEmailEnable.description: E-mail functionality for sending a message when an event occurred.

snEmailAddress.name: snEmailAddress
snEmailAddress.description: E-mail address to which messages will be sent.

snIpAddress.name: snIpAddress
snIpAddress.description: IP address of the agent. Changes become valid after restart.

snIpSubnetMask.name: snIpSubnetMask
snIpSubnetMask.description: IP subnet mask of the agent. Changes become valid after restart.

snIpDefaultGateway.name: snIpDefaultGateway
snIpDefaultGateway.description: IP address of the default gateway. Changes become valid after restart.

snBootP.name: snBootP
snBootP.description: Enable/Disable BOOTP. Changes become valid after restart.

snOsmFaultState.name: snOsmFaultState

snOsmFaultValue.description: Fault value: 0 = no fault, bit 0 = power, bit 1 = linkdown, bit 2 = internal error, bit 3 = standby, bit 4 = rm, bit 5 = dip switch rm, bit 6 = dip switch standby, bit 7 = ncm, bit 8 = partition port 1, ... bit 15 = partition port 8, bit 16 = observer error, bit 17 = non-recoverable ring error, bit 18 = reset to factory defaults

snOsmRmStateChanges.name: snOsmRmStateChanges
snOsmRmStateChanges.description: Number of changes to RM active state.

snOsmStandbyStateChanges.name: snOsmStandbyStateChanges
snOsmStandbyStateChanges.description: Number of changes to standby active state.

snOsmPort8TestMac.description: MAC (source) address of test telegrams sent on port 8.

snOsmMulticastTestMac.name: snOsmMulticastTestMac
snOsmMulticastTestMac.description: MAC multicast address used for redundancy functions.

snOsmMulticastLinkMac.name: snOsmMulticastLinkMac
snOsmMulticastLinkMac.description: MAC multicast address used for redundancy functions.

snOsmUnicastLinkMac.name: snOsmUnicastLinkMac
snOsmUnicastLinkMac.description: MAC unicast address used for redundancy functions.

snOsmMulticastSyncMac.name: snOsmMulticastSyncMac
snOsmMulticastSyncMac.description: MAC multicast address of time synchronisation packets.

snOsmMulticastFlowControlMac.name: snOsmMulticastFlowControlMac
snOsmMulticastFlowControlMac.description: MAC multicast address of flow control packets.

snOsmTestMaxDelay.name: snOsmTestMaxDelay
snOsmTestMaxDelay.description: Measured maximum delay of RM test telegrams.

snOsmPortTable.description: Table containing per-port objects in the form of private extensions of interface objects.
